<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="666" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12997</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 3402</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-01">March 1, 1935</date>.<lb/>[Received March
                                23.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Transportation of Chinese Troops on American
                            Vessels on the Upper Yangtze</p>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the
                            Legation’s despatch No. 3373 of February 19, 1935,<note n="86" xml:id="d666fn86">Not printed.</note> in regard to the
                            above-mentioned subject, and to enclose for the information of the
                            Department a copy of despatch No. 53, dated February 25, 1935, from the
                            Consul General at Hankow.<note n="86" xml:id="d666fn1">Not
                                printed.</note></p>
                        <p>Mr. Josselyn reports in this despatch that no Chinese troops have been
                            transported to Szechwan Province by American vessels, but that one
                            American vessel carried a certain amount of ammunition to that
                            region.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">C. E.
                                Gauss</hi></signed><lb/><hi rend="italic">Counselor of
                            Legation</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>